    "content": "The repo-wide architecture hierarchy is now materially balanced at the top level: every direct child of `concept://prism_architecture` has at least one internal child concept, and most major subsystems now split into reusable module-level packets. Important newer boundaries are the IR trio (`concept://graph_identity_and_parse_ir`, `concept://anchor_change_and_lineage_ir`, `concept://plan_and_coordination_ir`), the persistence trio (`concept://sqlite_and_graph_persistence`, `concept://memory_projection_persistence`, `concept://history_snapshot_and_resolution`), the compact-tool pair (`concept://compact_discovery_and_opening`, `concept://compact_expansion_and_concept_views`), the CLI pair, the dashboard pair, the validation pair, and the inference branch `concept://inferred_edge_runtime_and_session_store`. Future sessions should traverse these concept packets before reopening crate facades.",
